name: 20 by 30 Camouflage Tarp
description:
This Green Camouflage polyethylene tarp is a full finished size opposed to other "cut size" tarps.

The heavy duty industrial polyethylene material is 2.9oz/sq.yrd., 10 X 8 cross weave, and laminated on both sides for maximum weatherproofing and tear resistance.

Dry Top polyethylene tarps are laminated on both sides for maximum weather proofing; cross weave fabric is designed for maximum strength and durability.

High strength rust resistant grommets on each corner and approximately every 3 feet, lightweight, tear resistant, washable, mildew proof and water proof.

TRUE SIZED TARPS! All stated tarp dimensions are given for hemmed tarps.

name: 28 by 48 Silver/Brown Heavy Duty Tarp
description:
Our silver/brown tarp is used for sun protection on many different applications. The silver/brown poly tarp is built with a heavy U.V. treatment that helps reflect the sun, and is built with a super heavy duty 14 by 14 weave. The silver/brown tarp is used by landscapers, roofers, agriculture, boating, camping, industry, and any place you want to use a really strong tarp.

5.5 oz/sq.yard, 14 x 14 weave count

Heat Sealed Seams. Rope Reinforced Hems

Mildew resistant, Rot resistant, Waterproof

Tear and Acid Resistant. Artic Flexibility

Heavy duty solid plastic reinforced corners.

High strength rust-resistant grommets on each corner and approximately every 18 inches.

UV treated both sides

Tarp is full finished size, is not cut size
